                <span class="">Udel Stopnitsky</span>:
            </span>
            <span class="utterance" who="stopnitskyU" start="792.689" end="x">I was committing them to burial. I participated in burying them because I had a post of raid watchman because in German a "raid watchman" was active in air raids, and we too had to do that, so I had the right to take those people and to bury them. I still know to this day where the graves are located, because at the end I was the deputy [he says president] of the religious contingents of <a class="placename" href="#vothL101">Bedzin</a>, now . . .</span>
        </li>
