            <span class="utterance" who="stopnitskyU" start="1456.540" end="x">Only Jews. There were other <a class="term" href="#vothG_lager">lagers</a> in <a class="placename" href="#vothC4" type="camp">Auschwitz</a> where they had Poles, Gypsies, and Germans as well. Germans who were opponents of the Hitler regime were also sent to <a class="placename" href="#vothL90">Oświe̜cim</a>; [apparently a strange association of the Polish language with the Christian prisoners while the name <a class="placename" href="#vothC4" type="camp">Auschwitz</a> was the German-Jewish name]. But these were entirely separate <a class="term" href="#vothG_lager">lagers</a>.</span>
        </li>
                <li>
            <span class="who">
