            </span>
            <span class="utterance" who="stopnitskyU" start="1486.219" end="x">. . . the mother, [correcting himself] the mother-in-law went "on the automobile" [that obviously designates to the gas chamber] and my sister also went "on the automobile," and my sister-in-law also went "on the automobile". And although she was eighteen years old but she did not look so well in her face, she was what they called a <a class="term" href="#vothG_mussulman">Mussulman</a> [by this name they called people emaciated to the very bones, the name <a class="term" href="#vothG_mussulman">Mussulman</a> for this type of people was common in the <a class="term" href="#vothG_lager">lagers</a>; the origin is not known, some attribute it to the similarity in looks between these emaciated people and Gandhi or the Oriental beggars in general.]</span>
        </li>
                <li>
            <span class="who">
                <span class="">David Boder</span>:
            </span>
            <span class="utterance" who="boderD" start="1500.731" end="x">Yes.</span>
        </li>
