                <strong>Location:</strong>
                Sighetu Marmaţiei, Romania<br />
                            </p>
                            <div>
                Sighet&#226;s Jews were ordered to enter a ghetto in April and early May of 1944, with its population soon reaching almost 13,000 when rural Jews were added. The ghetto was liquidated when the Jews were deported to Auschwitz in four transports between May 16 and 22, 1944.
            </div>
